Amanda Khoza and Jenni Evans, News24Middelburg - Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane had to be whisked away from an angry crowd closing in on him at a community meeting in Mpumalanga on Friday."You cannot come to another man's yard and do as you please," shouted one man at Zwane as the meeting degenerated into people shouting and booing at the minister.Zwane was supposed to be discussing the recently unveiled Mining Charter, which ups the percentage of black ownership to 30%.But people attending the imbizo at the Sydney Choma Community Hall in Middelburg would not let him speak.More to follow.#MiningCharter: Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane says he is not embarrassed at all about the disruptions. @News24 @Fin24 pic.twitter.com/xeo3O7YMiH#MiningCharter: A rather unexpected twist here at what was supposed to be a Mining Charter Imbizo in Mpumalanga. @News24 @Fin24 pic.twitter.com/5u2KlcX9pL&mdash; Amanda Khoza (@MandaKhoza) June 23, 2017#MiningCharter: Things are a bit tense at the local community in Mpumalanga where the MC Imbizo was supposed to take place. @News24 @Fin24 pic.twitter.com/ga2JSXVSDz&mdash; Amanda Khoza (@MandaKhoza) June 23, 2017#MiningCharter: The situation is getting out of control. The crowd is angry. @News24 @Fin24 pic.twitter.com/ddXDiGLMST&mdash; Amanda Khoza (@MandaKhoza) June 23, 2017#MiningCharter: A rather unexpected twist here at what was supposed to be a Mining Charter Imbizo in Mpumalanga. @News24 @Fin24 pic.twitter.com/5u2KlcX9pL#MiningCharter: Things are a bit tense at the local community in Mpumalanga where the MC Imbizo was supposed to take place. @News24 @Fin24 pic.twitter.com/ga2JSXVSDz&mdash; Amanda Khoza (@MandaKhoza) June 23, 2017#MiningCharter: The situation is getting out of control. The crowd is angry. @News24 @Fin24 pic.twitter.com/ddXDiGLMST&mdash; Amanda Khoza (@MandaKhoza) June 23, 2017#MiningCharter: Things are a bit tense at the local community in Mpumalanga where the MC Imbizo was supposed to take place